<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12181a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12181a">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12181a"> 181(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> poledriven cot / (rapids)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Yet to understand the beauty and the charm of that characteristic piece of Irish landscape <font color="green">[From Killaloe to Limerick]</font>, you should be taken down the stream in the characteristic boat of those waters, the long <mark>pole-driven cot</mark> <font color="green">[small boat]</font>. Shooting the <mark>rapids</mark> in these crafts is a wonderful sensation, and even on a chill day in February the tumult of lashing water sends warmth into the blood. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGWM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SGWM"><cite title="source">Munster</cite></a> (1911) 16-17</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
